WEBVTT

00:27.427 --> 00:29.029
( exhales )

00:29.029 --> 00:31.431
MRS. WEIDEMEYER?

00:31.431 --> 00:33.433
IT'S ME, SASHA.
YOUR NEIGHBOR.

00:33.433 --> 00:35.836
ARE YOU HOME?

00:35.836 --> 00:38.038
COME ON, YOU OLD CRONE.
YOU'RE ALWAYS HOME.

00:38.038 --> 00:41.041
GINNY, HEY. IT'S ME.
I JUST GOT HOME

00:41.041 --> 00:42.442
AND MY FRONT DOOR
IS WIDE OPEN.

00:42.442 --> 00:45.045
NOT SURE WHAT TO DO.
CALL ME.

00:45.045 --> 00:47.047
<i>( phone beeps )</i>

00:47.047 --> 00:49.049
MRS. WEIDEMEYER,

00:49.049 --> 00:50.490
IF YOU'RE THERE
AND YOU HEARD

00:50.490 --> 00:52.052
THAT UNFORTUNATE
VERBAL SLIP I JUST MADE,

00:52.052 --> 00:53.614
I'M VERY SORRY,
IT CAME OUT OF THE MOMENT,

00:53.614 --> 00:55.215
AND I WANT TO
MAKE IT UP TO YOU.

00:55.215 --> 00:57.057
I THINK YOU HAVE
AN MRI NEXT WEEK?

00:57.057 --> 00:58.458
LOVE TO BE YOUR WHEELS.

01:02.062 --> 01:04.064
BOO? NOT THERE. OKAY.

01:04.064 --> 01:05.626
WHAT GOOD ARE CELLPHONES?

01:05.626 --> 01:07.187
LOOK, THERE MIGHT BE
A BURGLAR IN MY PLACE.

01:07.187 --> 01:08.068
CALL ME.

01:12.272 --> 01:13.473
<i>( phone beeps )</i>

01:13.473 --> 01:15.075
CALL POLICE.

01:15.075 --> 01:17.077
Phone:
<i>Calling Paula. Mobile.</i>

01:17.077 --> 01:19.079
‐ CANCEL.
‐ <i>( phone beeps )</i>

01:19.079 --> 01:20.881
CALL POLICE.

01:20.881 --> 01:23.524
Phone: <i>Calling Paulito's</i>
<i>Trattoria. Work.</i>

01:23.524 --> 01:25.085
‐ CANCEL.
‐ <i>( phone beeps )</i>

01:25.085 --> 01:27.247
CALL POLICE.

01:27.247 --> 01:28.809
Phone: <i>Calling Paul's</i>
<i>Bakery. Work.</i>

01:32.893 --> 01:35.175
<i>( theme music playing )</i>

01:53.113 --> 01:54.995
OH.

01:56.517 --> 01:57.838
‐ MM. DELICIOUS.
‐ HEAVEN.

01:57.838 --> 01:59.119
‐ WHOA.
‐ WHAT?

01:59.119 --> 02:00.841
‐ I THINK I JUST SAW GOD.
‐ FROM EATING A MARSHMALLOW?

02:00.841 --> 02:02.603
‐ HIS WAYS ARE STRANGE.
‐ WHAT DID HE LOOK LIKE?

02:02.603 --> 02:04.765
‐ JUDY GARLAND.
‐ GOD'S A GOOD GIG FOR HER.

02:04.765 --> 02:06.286
YOU'RE FALLING BEHIND,
TRULY.

02:06.286 --> 02:07.848
COME.
HAVE ANOTHER ONE.

02:07.848 --> 02:09.289
YOU KNOW THE OLD SAYING.

02:09.289 --> 02:11.011
"MY HIPS SAY NO,
BUT MY MOUTH SAYS

02:11.011 --> 02:12.452
GET IN THERE, TRULY,
AND ENJOY SOMETHING

02:12.452 --> 02:14.134
WITHOUT FEELING
THE LIFE‐SUCKING GUILT

02:14.134 --> 02:15.736
YOUR MOTHER BEAT INTO YOU
FOR 20 YEARS."

02:15.736 --> 02:17.137
IS THAT HOW
THE OLD SAYING GOES?

02:17.137 --> 02:18.378
‐ WORD FOR WORD.
‐ <i>( cellphone ringing )</i>

02:18.378 --> 02:21.301
COOLNESS. A TEXT
FROM MY FIANCE.

02:21.301 --> 02:23.544
OH, THEY CAN TEXT ON
LIFE ALERT PENDANTS
NOW?

02:23.544 --> 02:24.945
IGNORING THAT.

02:24.945 --> 02:26.947
HE'S ALL PACKED AND READY
TO DRIVE OUT HERE TOMORROW.

02:26.947 --> 02:28.228
HIS BEST MAN'S
RIDING SHOTGUN.

02:28.228 --> 02:29.710
THEY HAVE BEEN FRIENDS
SINCE GRADE SCHOOL.

02:29.710 --> 02:31.431
‐ ISN'T THAT CUTE?
‐ THEY CAN REMINISCE
ABOUT SOUP LINES

02:31.431 --> 02:32.753
AND ICE WAGONS.

02:32.753 --> 02:34.955
BEST MAN? WHEN ARE YOU
AND RICK GETTING MARRIED?

02:34.955 --> 02:36.877
TOMORROW.
ON THE BEACH AT SUNSET.

02:36.877 --> 02:38.559
RECEPTION TO FOLLOW
AT THE MADONNA INN.

02:38.559 --> 02:40.160
THE WEIRDEST, COOLEST
PLACE IN CALI.

02:40.160 --> 02:44.044
AH, GIRLS, YOU KNOW WHAT
MARRYING A LOVELY MAN OF
MEANS MEANS?

02:44.044 --> 02:46.166
NO MORE PERFORMING.
I CAN HANG UP THE TIGHTS,

02:46.166 --> 02:48.408
HANG UP THE HEADDRESSES.
DO YOU KNOW I HAVE WORKED

02:48.408 --> 02:50.330
EVERY NEW YEAR'S EVE
SINCE I WAS 17?

02:50.330 --> 02:52.172
I HAVE NEVER
CELEBRATED NEW YEAR'S.

02:52.172 --> 02:54.014
NOW RICK AND I CAN
CELEBRATE NEW YEAR'S.

02:54.014 --> 02:55.175
All: IF HE MAKES IT
TO NEW YEAR'S.

02:55.175 --> 02:57.057
‐ SO OBVIOUS.
‐ GETTING SLOPPY.

02:57.057 --> 02:58.338
AND I CAN CRAFT.

02:58.338 --> 02:59.259
I'VE ALWAYS
WANTED TO CRAFT.

02:59.259 --> 03:00.701
YOU HAVE NEVER
WANTED TO CRAFT.

03:00.701 --> 03:02.823
WELL, I DO NOW.
IT'LL BE DIRTY CRAFTING,

03:02.823 --> 03:04.184
BUT IT'LL BE CRAFTING.

03:04.184 --> 03:06.186
AND I DON'T HAVE TO GO
TO THE GYM SIX DAYS A WEEK.

03:06.186 --> 03:08.188
I CAN EVEN GAIN
THREE POUNDS.

03:08.188 --> 03:10.711
‐ THINK ABOUT THAT!
‐ I'D STILL LOVE YOU
IF YOU GAINED FIVE.

03:10.711 --> 03:12.432
AND I CAN GET A PACK
OF PEKINGESE TO GREET
ME AT THE DOOR

03:12.432 --> 03:14.995
WHEN I COME HOME FROM
NOT WORKING OR WORKING OUT.

03:14.995 --> 03:17.998
AND I CAN FEED THEM FROM
MY GIANT BOWL OF BONBONS.

03:17.998 --> 03:20.000
WHAT'S A PEKINGESE?
LONG‐HAIRED DOG?

03:20.000 --> 03:21.682
SHORT HAIR.
I THINK, YEAH. SHORT.

03:21.682 --> 03:22.763
AND YOU WON'T
MISS PERFORMING?

03:22.763 --> 03:24.204
THAT'S YOUR THING,
NOT MINE.

03:24.204 --> 03:25.566
BECAUSE RICK'S
YOUR THING NOW.

03:25.566 --> 03:26.727
RICK'S MY THING.

03:26.727 --> 03:28.368
AND MICHELLE'S
YOUR MAID OF HONOR?

03:28.368 --> 03:30.290
OH, WE DIDN'T EVEN
TALK ABOUT THAT.

03:30.290 --> 03:31.331
I'LL DO IT
IF YOU WANT ME TO?

03:31.331 --> 03:32.773
BECAUSE MAID OF HONOR

03:32.773 --> 03:34.615
IS AN IMPORTANT PART
OF ANY WEDDING, I THINK.

03:34.615 --> 03:36.216
WITH THE SYMBOLISM,

03:36.216 --> 03:39.379
AND THE EXPRESSIONISM,
AND THE CEREMONIALISM,

03:39.379 --> 03:40.420
AND THE DALAI‐LAMA‐ISM.

03:40.420 --> 03:41.942
WHERE'S SHE
GOING WITH THIS?

03:41.942 --> 03:43.143
ONE OF THOSE
WASN'T EVEN A WORD.

03:43.143 --> 03:45.305
I JUST THINK
YOU SHOULD HAVE

03:45.305 --> 03:47.227
A DESIGNATED
MAID OF HONOR.

03:47.227 --> 03:49.630
I WOULD BE A GREAT
MAID OF HONOR.

03:49.630 --> 03:52.032
NO ONE'S EVER ASKED ME.
BUT THEY SHOULD.

03:52.032 --> 03:53.233
BECAUSE I WOULD BE GREAT.

03:53.233 --> 03:55.435
IF I DO SAY SO MYSELF,
WHICH I JUST DID.

03:55.435 --> 03:57.037
‐ OH, YOU GOTTA.
‐ YOU DON'T MIND?

03:57.037 --> 03:58.478
LOOK AT THAT FACE.

03:59.560 --> 04:01.041
TRULY,

04:01.041 --> 04:02.843
WILL YOU BE MY
MAID OF HONOR?

04:02.843 --> 04:04.645
YES! REALLY?
I'LL BE A GREAT ONE.

04:04.645 --> 04:06.246
I JUST SAID THAT,
DIDN'T I?

04:06.246 --> 04:07.568
WE NEED MORE CHOCOLATE.

04:07.568 --> 04:09.249
MORE CHOCOLATE
COMING UP.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.411
IS SHE GONNA REMEMBER
SHE ASKED TOMORROW?

04:11.411 --> 04:12.492
VERY IFFY.

04:15.335 --> 04:16.256
‐ SASHA?
‐ AAH!

04:16.256 --> 04:17.257
I'M SORRY.
ARE YOU OKAY?

04:17.257 --> 04:19.059
I LOCKED THAT
THIS MORNING FOR SURE.

04:19.059 --> 04:20.060
I REMEMBER DOING IT.

04:20.060 --> 04:21.261
DID YOU CALL
THE POLICE?

04:21.261 --> 04:22.422
YES, AFTER BEING
ON HOLD FOR 20 MINUTES

04:22.422 --> 04:23.504
THEY TOLD ME TO
GO IN AND SEE IF

04:23.504 --> 04:24.745
ANYONE'S THERE.

04:24.745 --> 04:26.507
‐ THAT'S STUPID.
‐ I WAS DISAPPOINTED.

04:26.507 --> 04:29.069
WELL, IT'S PROBABLY
NOTHING.

04:29.069 --> 04:30.831
I'LL GO IN AND MAKE SURE
IT'S ALL FINE.

04:30.831 --> 04:32.072
I LOCKED THAT DOOR.

04:32.072 --> 04:33.674
‐ I BELIEVE YOU.
‐ BE CAREFUL.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.437
DON'T STEP
ON MY FRUIT!

04:37.437 --> 04:39.279
IT'S AN ORANGE.
WHO CARES?

04:39.279 --> 04:40.681
IT'S A TANGELO.
IT'S ORGANIC,

04:40.681 --> 04:42.082
AND IT COST LIKE
A THOUSAND DOLLARS.

04:42.082 --> 04:44.084
OKAY. I'LL WATCH
THE TANGELOS.

04:48.288 --> 04:49.690
‐ WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
‐ I'M COMING WITH.

04:49.690 --> 04:50.851
‐ NO.
‐ I CAN HELP.

04:50.851 --> 04:52.292
‐ I KNOW THE PLACE.
‐ I KNOW THE PLACE TOO.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.453
I KNOW IT BETTER.

04:53.453 --> 04:54.935
IT'S A ONE BEDROOM
APARTMENT.

04:54.935 --> 04:56.176
IT'S NOT LIKE YOU NEED
THE SCHEMATICS OR ANYTHING.

04:56.176 --> 04:58.699
‐ I'M GOING WITH YOU.
‐ FINE.

04:58.699 --> 05:00.701
ANYONE THERE?

05:00.701 --> 05:03.303
IF YOU'RE THERE,
YOU'RE GONNA WISH
YOU WEREN'T.

05:03.303 --> 05:05.666
OH, GOOD. THAT WAS GOOD.
NICE FORCEFUL TONE.

05:07.868 --> 05:11.311
LISTEN, THERE'S
A BASEBALL BAT
UNDER THE COUCH.

05:11.311 --> 05:12.873
I DON'T NEED
A BASEBALL BAT.

05:12.873 --> 05:14.474
AND THERE'S AN UMBRELLA
IN THE LINEN CLOSET.

05:14.474 --> 05:16.476
IT'S GOT PRETTY PONY ON IT,
BUT THE END'S REALLY POINTY.

05:16.476 --> 05:17.477
YOU CAN POKE
HIS EYES OUT.

05:17.477 --> 05:18.879
HELLO?

05:18.879 --> 05:20.320
THERE'S A TENNIS RACKET
BY THE FIREPLACE

05:20.320 --> 05:21.722
AND THERE'S AMMONIA
UNDER THE SINK.

05:21.722 --> 05:23.123
SO WE CAN DISINFECT HIM?

05:23.123 --> 05:25.125
BLIND HIM.
THEN WE'LL OVERTAKE HIM.

05:25.125 --> 05:26.727
UNLESS HE FOUND
THE PRETTY PONY UMBRELLA,

05:26.727 --> 05:28.128
IN WHICH CASE
WE'RE DONE FOR.

05:30.330 --> 05:32.332
WAS THIS DOOR CLOSED
WHEN YOU LEFT?

05:32.332 --> 05:33.574
YES.

05:33.574 --> 05:35.736
NO.
I DON'T REMEMBER.

05:38.138 --> 05:39.339
GET THE PRETTY PONY.

05:53.353 --> 05:56.356
‐ <i>( banging, clanging )</i>
‐ AAH! ROMAN!

06:00.761 --> 06:02.763
THERE IS A VERY LARGE
SPIDER IN THAT BATHROOM.

06:02.763 --> 06:04.444
A SPIDER?

06:04.444 --> 06:06.767
I MEAN, WE'RE TALKING
PALEOLITHIC HORROR MOVIE
TYPE STUFF HERE.

06:06.767 --> 06:08.008
WHERE'S MY UMBRELLA?

06:08.008 --> 06:09.169
HE TOOK IT FROM ME.

06:09.169 --> 06:11.371
THIS IS A VERY
SERIOUS SPIDER.

06:11.371 --> 06:13.173
WHAT ABOUT THE BEDROOM?

06:13.173 --> 06:14.775
( exhales )

06:14.775 --> 06:16.176
LET'S CHECK IT.

06:24.384 --> 06:26.106
THERE'S ANOTHER
BASEBALL BAT IN
THE CLOSET

06:26.106 --> 06:27.948
AND THERE'S A CROWBAR
UNDER THE BED.

06:27.948 --> 06:30.190
REMIND ME NEVER TO
MAKE YOU MAD AT ME.

06:40.200 --> 06:41.802
‐ ( sighs )
‐ ANYTHING?

06:41.802 --> 06:43.403
JUST THE CROWBAR.

06:43.403 --> 06:44.645
I THINK WE'RE GOOD.

06:44.645 --> 06:46.807
‐ WE'RE GOOD?
‐ WE'RE GOOD.

06:46.807 --> 06:48.609
GOOD.

06:48.609 --> 06:51.211
‐ THANK YOU FOR COMING.
‐ ANYTIME.

06:51.211 --> 06:53.413
I'VE NEVER LEFT
THAT DOOR OPEN.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.055
THAT WAS SO STUPID.

06:55.055 --> 06:56.817
YEAH.
YOU SHOULD WATCH THAT.

06:56.817 --> 06:59.419
I KNOW YOU
COULDN'T TELL,

06:59.419 --> 07:01.221
BUT I WAS SCARED.

07:01.221 --> 07:02.302
I COULD TELL.

07:04.424 --> 07:05.506
YOUR HANDS ARE COLD.

07:05.506 --> 07:06.827
THEY'RE ALWAYS COLD.

07:12.833 --> 07:14.434
WE SHOULD GO CHECK
ON MRS. WEIDEMEYER.

07:14.434 --> 07:15.836
SHE MIGHT BE DEAD.

07:15.836 --> 07:17.437
MRS. WEIDEMEYER'S FINE.

07:25.606 --> 07:27.327
<i>WE'RE HERE!</i>
<i>SASHA, IT'S RUSTY!</i>

07:27.327 --> 07:28.929
<i>‐ AND NANETTE!</i>
<i>‐ THE JORDANS!</i>

07:28.929 --> 07:30.851
RUSTY AND NANETTE JORDAN.

07:30.851 --> 07:32.452
‐ OH, THANK GOD.
‐ ARE YOU OKAY?

07:32.452 --> 07:34.254
WHO IS THIS BOY?
DO WE KNOW THIS BOY?

07:34.254 --> 07:35.696
‐ I DON'T KNOW THIS BOY.
‐ THIS IS ROMAN. HE GOT
HERE FIRST.

07:35.696 --> 07:37.538
‐ DID YOU CHECK
ALL THE ROOMS?
‐ ALL THE CLOSETS?

07:37.538 --> 07:38.859
‐ THE BATHROOMS?
‐ <i>THE CUPBOARDS?</i>

07:38.859 --> 07:40.180
YEAH.
WE CHECKED IT ALL.

07:40.180 --> 07:41.461
‐ <i>OH, THANK GOD.</i>
‐ I WANT TO MAKE SURE.

07:41.461 --> 07:42.943
‐ DO WE KNOW THIS BOY?
‐ YEAH, WE KNOW HIM.

07:42.943 --> 07:44.464
‐ OH MY GOD.
‐ SHE'S OKAY.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.866
‐ YOU'RE OKAY?
‐ I'M OKAY.

07:45.866 --> 07:47.467
‐ HI, ROMAN.
‐ HI, BOO.

07:47.467 --> 07:48.869
SO WE KNOW THIS BOY?

07:48.869 --> 07:50.030
YES, WE KNOW THIS BOY.

07:50.030 --> 07:51.471
‐ RUSTY?
‐ <i>I'M DOING A SWEEP.</i>

07:51.471 --> 07:52.553
WE WERE SO WORRIED.

07:52.553 --> 07:54.114
‐ I'M OKAY.
‐ <i>LIVING ROOM'S CLEAR.</i>

07:54.114 --> 07:56.557
<i>‐ I'LL CHECK THE KITCHEN.</i>
<i>‐ I GOT THE KITCHEN.</i>

07:56.557 --> 07:57.558
DID YOU LOOK
UNDER THE BED?

07:57.558 --> 07:58.679
THAT'S WHERE THEY HIDE,
UNDER THE BED.

07:58.679 --> 08:00.240
I CHECKED
UNDER THE BED.

08:00.240 --> 08:01.562
‐ I'M GONNA CHECK THE BATHROOM.
‐ YEAH, CHECK THE BATHROOM.

08:01.562 --> 08:03.043
WHERE'D YOU HAVE
THE SLEDGEHAMMER?

08:03.043 --> 08:04.364
OH, I BROUGHT
THE SLEDGEHAMMER.

08:04.364 --> 08:06.607
Boys: ( yelling )

08:06.607 --> 08:09.009
YOU HAD TO BRING
THE WINKLEBURNS?

08:09.009 --> 08:10.731
IT WOULDN'T BE SAFE
TO LEAVE THEM IN THE CAR.

08:10.731 --> 08:11.972
YOU THOUGHT THERE WAS
A BURGLAR IN HERE.

08:11.972 --> 08:13.053
THAT IS SAFER?

08:13.053 --> 08:14.575
Rusty: <i>OH, GEEZ.</i>
<i>WHAT THE GEEZ!</i>

08:14.575 --> 08:16.577
‐ RUSTY, WHAT'S HAPPENING?!
‐ <i>IT'S THE BIGGEST SPIDER</i>

08:16.577 --> 08:18.498
<i>I'VE EVER SEEN IN HERE.</i>
<i>IT'S A MONSTER!</i>

08:18.498 --> 08:20.581
‐ WELL, KILL IT!
‐ <i>I TRIED. IT WON'T DIE!</i>

08:20.581 --> 08:22.623
WELL‐‐ BOO, GET
THE WINKLEBURNS.

08:22.623 --> 08:24.705
Rusty:
<i>OH, IT'S LOOKING RIGHT AT ME.</i>

08:24.705 --> 08:26.827
<i>‐ SMASH IT WITH</i>
<i>YOUR SLEDGEHAMMER.</i>
<i>‐ IT TOOK THE SLEDGEHAMMER!</i>

08:26.827 --> 08:29.510
<i>‐ CAN YOU JUMP OUT THE WINDOW?</i>
<i>‐ I CAN'T GET OUT THE WINDOW!</i>

08:29.510 --> 08:30.751
<i>IT'S GOT TEETH!</i>

08:30.751 --> 08:32.913
Michelle:
<i>FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.</i>

08:32.913 --> 08:34.915
<i>( piano playing )</i>

08:38.318 --> 08:39.680
GOOD, GUYS.
LET'S DO IT AGAIN.

08:41.081 --> 08:42.523
WHERE ARE YOU SPOTTING?

08:42.523 --> 08:44.324
MICHELLE,
STRAPS OR STRAPLESS?

08:44.324 --> 08:45.926
‐ WHAT?
‐ FOR MY MAID OF HONOR DRESS.

08:45.926 --> 08:47.688
I'M MAKING IT
STRAPS OR STRAPLESS?

08:47.688 --> 08:49.610
I DON'T KNOW.
STRAPS, I GUESS.

08:49.610 --> 08:51.051
LIKE MINDS.

08:51.051 --> 08:52.172
REALLY USE YOUR FEET.

08:52.172 --> 08:53.173
WIDE OR SPAGHETTI?

08:53.173 --> 08:54.535
WIDE. GO WIDE.

08:54.535 --> 08:57.337
WE ARE SIMPATICO.

08:57.337 --> 08:58.699
LAND IN FIFTH,
PLEASE.

08:58.699 --> 09:00.100
TIME TO PICK A FABRIC,
PARTNER.

09:00.100 --> 09:01.942
TRULY, PLEASE.
CLASS ENDS IN 20 MINUTES.

09:01.942 --> 09:04.184
‐ WE'LL TALK THEN.
‐ I HAVE EIGHT HOURS
TO GET THIS MADE.

09:04.184 --> 09:05.706
MY FOCUS RIGHT NOW
IS HERE, OKAY?

09:05.706 --> 09:06.987
FAIR ENOUGH.

09:07.988 --> 09:09.349
Michelle: <i>NICE.</i>

09:09.349 --> 09:11.351
<i>USE YOUR PLIES.</i>

09:11.351 --> 09:13.353
I'M LEANING TOWARDS
THE CRINKLE CHIFFON.

09:13.353 --> 09:15.195
<i>TRULY, ASK TALIA.</i>
<i>SHE'S THE BRIDE.</i>

09:15.195 --> 09:17.037
I DID, BUT I WANT
A SECOND OPINION.

09:17.037 --> 09:18.639
IT'S A DRESS, NOT
A HIP REPLACEMENT.

09:18.639 --> 09:20.320
‐ <i>( whistle blows )</i>
‐ WHAT THE HELL?

09:20.320 --> 09:21.602
<i>‐ UH‐OH.</i>
<i>‐ BASH.</i>

09:21.602 --> 09:22.643
‐ WHAT ZONES?
‐ ZONES? WHAT DO YOU MEAN
ZONES?

09:22.643 --> 09:23.804
ZONE ONE?
I'M ZONE ONE.

09:23.804 --> 09:24.885
‐ I'M THREE.
‐ I'M FOUR.

09:24.885 --> 09:26.046
‐ I'M TWO.
‐ I'M LOST.

09:26.046 --> 09:28.448
THIS IS A FULL AND
IMMEDIATE EVACUATION,

09:28.448 --> 09:30.731
PEOPLE. ZONES
ONE THROUGH FOUR.

09:30.731 --> 09:32.813
( girls murmur )

09:32.813 --> 09:33.974
WHERE'S FANNY?

09:33.974 --> 09:35.095
OUT OF THE COUNTRY.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

09:35.095 --> 09:37.057
THE WOODS NORTH OF
THE HIGHWAY ARE ON FIRE.

09:37.057 --> 09:39.299
EVERYONE IN AN EVAC ZONE
NEEDS TO BE IN A SHELTER.

09:39.299 --> 09:41.221
OH, WOW. OKAY.
SO WHERE DO I GO?

09:41.221 --> 09:42.583
YOU'RE ALREADY THERE.

09:42.583 --> 09:43.904
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

09:43.904 --> 09:45.586
THE STUDIO IS ONE
OF TWO DESIGNATED

09:45.586 --> 09:47.588
EVACUATION CENTERS
IN TOWN.

09:47.588 --> 09:49.590
WE'RE THE EAST SIDE EVAC.
THEY'RE THE WEST SIDE.

09:49.590 --> 09:51.712
WAIT, SO PEOPLE
ARE COMING HERE
TO STAY? TO SLEEP?

09:51.712 --> 09:53.193
AND I'M ONE OF
THE ONES IN CHARGE.

09:53.193 --> 09:54.354
THAT'S WHY I'M
WEARING THIS CAP.

09:54.354 --> 09:55.956
‐ THAT SAYS "CAP."
‐ THAT'S RIGHT.

09:55.956 --> 09:57.077
THAT JUST SEEMS SILLY.

09:57.077 --> 09:58.599
CAP STANDS FOR CAPTAIN.

09:58.599 --> 09:59.840
IT IDENTIFIES MY AUTHORITY.

09:59.840 --> 10:01.522
YOU'D BETTER
CATCH UP HERE.

10:01.522 --> 10:03.764
HMM.
YOU'VE GOT A BIG HEAD,

10:03.764 --> 10:05.245
‐ BUT I THINK IT'LL FIT.
‐ THINK WHAT'LL FIT?

10:05.245 --> 10:06.767
THE "CAP" CAP.
IT COMES WITH THE JOB.

10:06.767 --> 10:09.409
WE'LL HAVE TO BROOM OUT
THESE CHAIRS HERE.

10:09.409 --> 10:10.490
WHAT JOB?

10:10.490 --> 10:11.692
WITH FANNY GONE,

10:11.692 --> 10:13.333
YOU ARE THE DESIGNATED
CO‐CAPTAIN

10:13.333 --> 10:14.935
OF THE EAST SIDE
EVACUATION CENTER.

10:14.935 --> 10:16.617
‐ NO. I REFUSE.
‐ YES. YOU CAN'T.

10:16.617 --> 10:18.939
‐ I'M UNQUALIFIED.
‐ SO WAS I, AND LOOK
AT ME NOW.

10:18.939 --> 10:20.100
THE TOWN IS DOOMED.

10:20.100 --> 10:22.022
LISTEN, TIME IS OF
THE ESSENCE HERE.

10:22.022 --> 10:23.704
THERE'S NO ONE
ELSE TO DO THIS.

10:23.704 --> 10:25.185
SO IF YOU CARE
ABOUT YOUR COMMUNITY,

10:25.185 --> 10:26.627
PUT THE "CAP" CAP ON.

10:32.032 --> 10:33.273
HEAD'S TOO BIG.

10:40.721 --> 10:42.643
SO ALL THE IMMEDIATE‐NEED
FOOD AND WATER SUPPLIES

10:42.643 --> 10:44.805
WILL BE SET UP AND DISPENSED
ALONG THE SOUTH WALL HERE.

10:44.805 --> 10:45.806
"FOOD AND WATER SUPPLIES."
GOT IT.

10:45.806 --> 10:47.287
‐ DON'T WRITE THAT DOWN.
‐ OKAY.

10:47.287 --> 10:49.209
AND THIS WILL BE LAPTOPS
WITH INTERNET CONNECTIONS

10:49.209 --> 10:50.811
SO PEOPLE CAN KEEP
IN TOUCH WITH LOVED ONES.

10:50.811 --> 10:51.972
"IN TOUCH WITH LOVED ONES."
SWEET.

10:51.972 --> 10:53.814
‐ DON'T WRITE THAT DOWN.
‐ CROSSING IT OFF.

10:53.814 --> 10:55.656
AND OVER THERE IS
OUR MEDICAL AREA.

10:55.656 --> 10:57.578
BANDAGES, IV, ANALGESICS,
ALL THE BASICS.

10:57.578 --> 10:58.939
"ALL THE BASICS."

10:58.939 --> 11:00.901
‐ DON'T WRITE THAT DOWN.
‐ WHY DID YOU GIVE
ME A CLIPBOARD?

11:00.901 --> 11:03.063
MOST OF THE REST OF
THIS SPACE WILL BE
SLEEPING AREAS.

11:03.063 --> 11:04.825
SO YOU AND I WILL
HAVE TO SIT DOWN

11:04.825 --> 11:07.147
AND FIGURE OUT HOW
TO DIVIDE PEOPLE UP.
MAKE A CHART.

11:07.147 --> 11:08.909
DIVIDE THEM UP?
MAKE A CHART? WHY?

11:08.909 --> 11:10.751
OBVIOUSLY FAMILIES
CAN STAY TOGETHER,

11:10.751 --> 11:12.392
BUT THE YOUNG UNMARRIED
SHOULDN'T MIX.

11:12.392 --> 11:14.234
COME ON, BASH,
IT'S ONE BIG OPEN ROOM.

11:14.234 --> 11:15.916
WHAT COULD THEY
POSSIBLY DO?

11:15.916 --> 11:17.237
ORGY.

11:17.237 --> 11:18.919
HAVE THEY ORGIED
IN THE PAST?

11:18.919 --> 11:20.000
THERE'S ALWAYS
A FIRST.

11:20.000 --> 11:21.922
WELL, THIS IS AMERICA,
LAND OF THE FREE.

11:21.922 --> 11:23.844
LET THE PEOPLE CHOOSE
WHERE THEY WANT TO SLEEP.

11:23.844 --> 11:25.846
FINE. YOUR CALL.
FOLLOW ME.

11:27.407 --> 11:29.570
HERE'S OUR SLUSH STORAGE.

11:29.570 --> 11:32.172
AND OF COURSE, SPACE FOR
OUR FOUR‐LEGGED EVACUEES.

11:32.172 --> 11:33.694
CAN YOU BE IN CHARGE
OF THEIR WATER?

11:33.694 --> 11:35.495
‐ I WILL WATER THE ANIMALS.
‐ BETTER WRITE THAT DOWN.

11:35.495 --> 11:36.857
‐ OH, GEEZ.
‐ OH, AND...

11:36.857 --> 11:38.258
I ALMOST FORGOT.
HERE.

11:38.258 --> 11:39.780
A WALKIE‐TALKIE.

11:39.780 --> 11:41.862
SO WE CAN COMMUNICATE.
WE'RE CO‐CAPTAINS,

11:41.862 --> 11:43.263
AND COMMUNICATION
IS VITAL.

11:43.263 --> 11:45.065
‐ OKAY.
‐ SO IT'S IMPORTANT...

11:45.065 --> 11:45.866
‐ FIRE TORPEDOES!
FIRE TORPEDOES!
‐ ...TO USE IT RESPONSIBLY

11:45.866 --> 11:47.107
BECAUSE IT'S
NOT A TOY.

11:47.107 --> 11:48.268
RIGHT.
NOT A TOY.

11:48.268 --> 11:49.510
IT'S GONNA BE
A LONG NIGHT, MICHELLE.

11:49.510 --> 11:50.791
AND I CAN'T
DO THIS ALONE.

11:50.791 --> 11:51.872
I'M HERE FOR YOU.

11:51.872 --> 11:56.276
REALLY BE HERE FOR ME AND
AT THE END OF THE NIGHT...

11:56.276 --> 11:58.278
WE'LL HAVE THIS
TO LOOK FORWARD TO.

11:58.278 --> 11:59.720
CHAMPAGNE.

11:59.720 --> 12:01.722
FOR WHEN THE FIRE'S OUT
AND EVERYONE'S OKAY.

12:01.722 --> 12:03.884
DO A GOOD JOB, AND YOU'LL
BE SIPPING IT WITH ME.

12:03.884 --> 12:05.606
I FEEL VERY
INCENTIVIZED.

12:05.606 --> 12:06.887
COME ON.
LET'S GET GOING.

12:10.050 --> 12:11.732
TIME TO START
CHECKING PEOPLE IN.

12:11.732 --> 12:14.054
‐ LET'S DO IT.
‐ JUST GET THE NAMES OF
EVERYBODY IN THE PARTY

12:14.054 --> 12:15.896
AND NOTE DOWN ANY
SPECIAL NEEDS. EASY?

12:15.896 --> 12:16.897
EASY PEASY.

12:16.897 --> 12:18.739
ALL RIGHT, EVERYBODY.
LET'S GET STARTED.

12:18.739 --> 12:20.460
WELCOME TO THE EAST SIDE
EVAC CENTER.

12:20.460 --> 12:21.982
‐ NAME PLEASE.
‐ FRANK BRADSHAW.

12:21.982 --> 12:24.304
I'M WITH MY WIFE NIKKI
AND MY DAUGHTER KIM.

12:24.304 --> 12:26.026
THE BRADSHAWS.
EXCELLENT.

12:26.026 --> 12:28.068
I'M BASH.
I'LL BE YOUR POINT PERSON.

12:28.068 --> 12:29.990
GRAB SOME COTS,
SET THEM UP WHERE YOU CAN,

12:29.990 --> 12:31.912
AND JUST KNOW THAT
ANYTHING YOU NEED
THAT'S GETABLE,

12:31.912 --> 12:33.473
‐ I'LL BE HERE TO
GET IT FOR YOU.
‐ THANKS, BASH.

12:33.473 --> 12:35.796
‐ AND I'M MICHELLE‐‐
‐ NEXT IN LINE, PLEASE?

12:35.796 --> 12:37.918
‐ <i>NAME PLEASE?</i>
‐ GEORGIE ATTENBURG.

12:37.918 --> 12:39.680
IT'LL BE ME
AND MY HUSBAND MORTY.

12:39.680 --> 12:42.082
THE ATTENBURGS.
GOT IT.

12:42.082 --> 12:43.644
GINNY, HI.
IT'S YOU AND YOUR MOM?

12:43.644 --> 12:44.885
OH, MY MOM'S
COMING LATER.

12:44.885 --> 12:47.087
HAPPY FIRE DAY.
STRIKE A POSE.

12:47.087 --> 12:49.009
ALL RIGHT,
GET OVER HERE, GUYS.
LET ME SIGN YOU IN.

12:49.009 --> 12:50.611
NO NEED TO
ASK THE NAMES.

12:50.611 --> 12:52.252
GINNY THOMPSON
AND MELANIE SEGAL,

12:52.252 --> 12:54.094
WELCOME TO THE
EAST SIDE EVAC CENTER.

12:54.094 --> 12:55.255
‐ I'LL BE YOUR POINT PERSON.
‐ BUP BUP BUP BUP.

12:55.255 --> 12:56.777
‐ WHAT, BASH? WHAT?
‐ SEGAL AND THOMPSON?

12:56.777 --> 12:58.098
THEY'RE WITH ME.

12:58.098 --> 12:59.780
YOU'VE GOT A MILLION
PEOPLE IN YOUR LINE,
BASH.

12:59.780 --> 13:02.342
‐ LET ME HELP.
‐ PEOPLE NEED TO CHECK IN
AT THE DESIGNATED TABLES.

13:02.342 --> 13:04.785
AND HOW HAVE YOU
DESIGNATED THESE
TABLES?

13:04.785 --> 13:06.947
FIRST LETTERS OF
THE LAST NAMES,
PER THE SIGNS.

13:06.947 --> 13:09.349
SIGN?
WHAT SIGN?

13:09.349 --> 13:11.351
X THROUGH Z?
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

13:11.351 --> 13:13.273
I THINK THAT'S A DOABLE
WORKLOAD FOR YOU.

13:13.273 --> 13:15.115
OH, COME ON.
WHERE'S THE TRUST?

13:15.115 --> 13:16.957
‐ WHERE'S THE CAP?
‐ IT'S TOO SMALL.

13:16.957 --> 13:18.839
‐ YOUR HEAD'S TOO BIG.
‐ HER HEAD IS NOT TOO BIG.

13:18.839 --> 13:20.000
YEAH, BACK OFF, MAN.

13:20.000 --> 13:21.121
I'M CHECKING THESE
TWO IN, OKAY?

13:21.121 --> 13:22.963
‐ I'M CHECKING THEM IN.
‐ I WISH YOU WOULDN'T.

13:22.963 --> 13:25.085
‐ GRAB YOURSELVES
A COUPLE OF COTS, GIRLS.
‐ THIS IS THE ROAD TO RUIN.

13:25.085 --> 13:26.166
AND YOU LET ME KNOW
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING.

13:26.166 --> 13:30.010
‐ THANKS, MICHELLE.
‐ YEAH. THANKS.

13:30.010 --> 13:31.812
SEGAL AND THOMPSON
ARE CHECKED IN.

13:31.812 --> 13:34.174
NOTED.
NEXT IN LINE, PLEASE?

13:34.174 --> 13:34.975
OH YEAH,
SAME HERE.

13:34.975 --> 13:36.136
WHO'S NEXT
IN MY LINE?

13:36.136 --> 13:38.058
I'M X, Y, Z.

13:38.058 --> 13:40.380
SO LET'S SEE...
WHERE IS THE YOGURTS?

13:40.380 --> 13:43.183
TOM AND PAM YOGURT?
LITTLE BILLY YOGURT?

13:43.183 --> 13:45.826
‐ ARE MY YOGURTS HERE?
‐ ROGER CHAMPLAIN AND
WIFE SISSY.

13:45.826 --> 13:47.027
HOW ABOUT ZACHARY ZIGZAG?

13:47.027 --> 13:49.429
YOU IN THE HOUSE ZACH?
WHERE IS THE ZIG MAN?

13:49.429 --> 13:51.231
MY NAME IS BASH
AND I'LL BE YOUR POINT PERSON.

13:51.231 --> 13:53.393
ANY ZOMBIES?
THAT STARTS WITH A "Z" RIGHT?

13:53.393 --> 13:56.036
ANYONE UNDEAD HERE?
ANY FLESH EATERS? NO?

13:56.036 --> 13:57.157
FINE, MICHELLE.

13:57.157 --> 13:58.839
CHAOS? IS THAT
WHAT YOU WANT?

13:58.839 --> 14:00.120
TOTAL AND COMPLETE CHAOS?

14:00.120 --> 14:01.441
BRING IT ON.

14:01.441 --> 14:03.043
FINE, WHAT THE HELL.

14:03.043 --> 14:05.325
EVERYONE JUST GET IN
WHATEVER LINE YOU WANT.

14:05.325 --> 14:06.406
GO.

14:09.049 --> 14:13.413
WOW.
ALTAMONT.

14:13.413 --> 14:14.414
LOOKS LIKE WE'VE
GOT OUR CHOICE.

14:14.414 --> 14:15.736
WHERE DO YOU
WANT TO SET UP?

14:15.736 --> 14:17.257
JUST KEEP ME AWAY FROM
THE DIRTY LITTLE CHILDREN.

14:17.257 --> 14:19.099
‐ HEY.
‐ SPEAKING OF WHICH.

14:19.099 --> 14:20.260
HEY, DEZ.

14:20.260 --> 14:22.863
SO, FIRE, HUH?

14:22.863 --> 14:24.024
YEAH, YOU SET IT?

14:24.024 --> 14:25.265
WHAT? NO.

14:25.265 --> 14:26.867
NOT THIS ONE.

14:26.867 --> 14:28.348
I DIDN'T SEE YOU IN LINE.
DID YOU CHECK IN?

14:28.348 --> 14:30.030
NO, I JUST SLID
UNDER THE FLAT

14:30.030 --> 14:31.431
BACK WHERE
THE ANIMALS GO.

14:31.431 --> 14:32.673
APPROPRIATE.

14:32.673 --> 14:34.274
SO, YOU TAKING PICTURES?

14:34.274 --> 14:36.036
YOUNG SHERLOCK
IS IN THE HOUSE.

14:36.036 --> 14:37.357
I WAS JUST SAYING.

14:39.680 --> 14:40.881
UMBILICAL CORD
CHOKED HIM?

14:40.881 --> 14:41.922
THAT'S WHAT
I'M THINKING.

14:49.890 --> 14:51.892
‐ THERE'S ROMAN.
‐ I KNOW.

14:51.892 --> 14:53.373
SO, YOU NEVER
ASKED MY OPINION,

14:53.373 --> 14:55.215
BUT IF YOU DID,
I'D SAY "YOWZA."

14:55.215 --> 14:56.697
THANK YOU,
LOUISE BROOKS.

14:56.697 --> 14:58.058
SEEMS LIKE IT'S
GETTING SERIOUS.

14:58.058 --> 15:00.140
VERY. WE'RE CONSIDERING
A REVERSE MORTGAGE.

15:00.140 --> 15:02.262
‐ REALLY?
‐ <i>BOO.</i>

15:02.262 --> 15:03.423
<i>HEY!</i>

15:03.423 --> 15:04.785
THERE'S MY
HUNKA HUNKA.

15:04.785 --> 15:06.186
REALLY? WHAT DECADE
DO YOU LIVE IN?

15:06.186 --> 15:07.387
EVERYBODY GOOD
AT YOUR HOUSE?

15:07.387 --> 15:08.468
DAD'S OUT
FIGHTING THE FIRE.

15:08.468 --> 15:09.630
EVERYONE ELSE
IS ON THE WAY.

15:09.630 --> 15:11.071
WELL, COME ON.
TAKE CUTS.

15:11.071 --> 15:12.993
‐ NO, I SHOULDN'T.
‐ I WANT YOU TO.

15:12.993 --> 15:14.154
IT'S NOT COOL
TO CUT IN.

15:14.154 --> 15:16.917
HEY, EVERYBODY. IS IT COOL
IF MY GIRLFRIEND CUTS IN?

15:16.917 --> 15:18.078
All: NO.

15:18.078 --> 15:19.680
I'LL CATCH UP
WITH YOU LATER.

15:19.680 --> 15:22.082
‐ HEY, CARL.
‐ HEY, MICHELLE.

15:22.082 --> 15:23.644
JEFF TOBEY.
MOTHER AND SISTER ARE

15:23.644 --> 15:24.725
WANDERING AROUND
HERE SOMEWHERE.

15:24.725 --> 15:25.806
JEFF TOBEY.

15:25.806 --> 15:27.007
ALL RIGHT. GOT YOU
DOWN HERE, FRIEND.

15:27.007 --> 15:28.408
I'LL BE YOUR
POINT PERSON TONIGHT.

15:28.408 --> 15:29.810
‐ COOL.
‐ I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE THINKING

15:29.810 --> 15:31.091
ALONG THE LINES
OF ENTERTAINMENT,

15:31.091 --> 15:32.292
<i>BUT IF THERE'S</i>
<i>A DVD PLAYER,</i>

15:32.292 --> 15:33.934
I HAVE THE MOST
UNDERRATED MOVIE

15:33.934 --> 15:36.096
OF THE PAST YEAR.
"HOPE SPRINGS."

15:36.096 --> 15:38.939
"HOPE SPRINGS"?
I LOVE THAT MOVIE.

15:38.939 --> 15:40.260
YEAH, WHAT'S
NOT TO LOVE?

15:40.260 --> 15:42.102
THE OSCARS SHOULD HAVE
BEEN ALL OVER THAT JOINT.

15:42.102 --> 15:43.103
YES!

15:43.103 --> 15:44.264
AT FIRST I WAS LIKE,

15:44.264 --> 15:45.746
"TWO MIDDLE‐AGED
EMPTY NESTERS

15:45.746 --> 15:48.348
TRYING TO REKINDLE THE SPARK
IN THEIR MARRIAGE? PASS."

15:48.348 --> 15:50.190
BUT WHO KNEW
TOMMY LEE JONES COULD BE

15:50.190 --> 15:51.952
SO TENDER
AND VULNERABLE.

15:51.952 --> 15:53.954
HE KICKED ASS.

15:53.954 --> 15:56.196
WHAT IS THAT THOUGH?
IT DOESN'T LOOK LIKE
THE ACTUAL DVD.

15:56.196 --> 15:58.358
IT'S NOT. I'VE GOT A COUSIN
WHO WORKS IN HOLLYWOOD

15:58.358 --> 16:00.961
AND THEY SEND HIM ALL
THESE FREE DVDS AT AWARDS TIME.

16:00.961 --> 16:02.843
WHY EVERY IDIOT WRITER
AND DIRECTOR IN HOLLYWOOD

16:02.843 --> 16:05.445
WANTS TO WATCH A FREE DVD
AND NOT SUPPORT THEIR INDUSTRY,

16:05.445 --> 16:07.447
I DON'T KNOW.
BUT HE BREAKS THE RULES

16:07.447 --> 16:09.369
AND GIVES THEM TO ME.
CHA‐CHING!

16:09.369 --> 16:11.211
"HELL YES, I WANT IT.

16:11.211 --> 16:12.893
YOU BET YOUR LIFE
I WANT IT."

16:12.893 --> 16:14.615
‐ WOW, THAT'S REALLY GOOD.
‐ THANKS.

16:14.615 --> 16:16.977
YEAH, BUT YOU SHOULD HIT
THE "IT" A LITTLE MORE.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.539
"HELL YES, I WANT IT.

16:18.539 --> 16:20.340
YOU BET YOUR LIFE
I WANT IT."

16:20.340 --> 16:22.543
AND YOU SHOULD HIT
THE "HELL YES" HARDER.

16:22.543 --> 16:23.784
LIKE TOMMY DOES.

16:23.784 --> 16:25.385
‐ "HELL YES."
‐ "HELL YES."

16:25.385 --> 16:28.228
‐ "HELL YES."
‐ "HELL YES."

16:28.228 --> 16:30.150
OKAY, COOL.

16:30.150 --> 16:31.872
THANKS FOR THE TIP.

16:31.872 --> 16:33.273
YEAH, SAME HERE.

16:33.273 --> 16:35.996
Talia: <i>MICHELLE?</i>

16:35.996 --> 16:37.397
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK,
EVERYBODY.

16:37.397 --> 16:39.239
OH HONEY,
YOUR WEDDING.

16:39.239 --> 16:40.561
MY GOD, THE TIMING
OF ALL THIS.

16:40.561 --> 16:42.242
‐ I KNOW.
‐ I WAS TALKING TO TALIA.

16:42.242 --> 16:44.004
SHE'S UPSET TOO.

16:44.004 --> 16:46.006
HAVE YOU TALKED TO RICK?
WE'LL RESCHEDULE, OKAY?

16:46.006 --> 16:47.568
‐ WE'LL DO IT NEXT MONTH?
‐ NEXT MONTH? NO.

16:47.568 --> 16:50.170
‐ WE'RE DOING IT TODAY.
‐ BUT HON, THE FIRE CUTS
US OFF FROM THE BEACH.

16:50.170 --> 16:52.172
I DON'T NEED THE BEACH.
ALL I NEED IS RICK AND
THE MINISTER.

16:52.172 --> 16:54.014
AND YOUR MAID OF HONOR,
AND I AM RIGHT HERE.

16:54.014 --> 16:55.936
‐ WE'RE DOING IT.
‐ Milly: <i>MICHELLE.</i>

16:55.936 --> 16:57.818
‐ <i>LET'S GO. A LOT OF</i>
<i>PEOPLE WAITING HERE.</i>
‐ COMING.

16:57.818 --> 16:59.259
WE'LL THINK
GOOD THOUGHTS.

17:00.741 --> 17:03.023
I DIDN'T SEE YOU
IN LINE BEFORE, MILLY.

17:03.023 --> 17:04.184
YOU DIDN'T CUT IN,
DID YOU?

17:04.184 --> 17:06.547
‐ NO. I WAS HERE.
‐ REALLY?

17:06.547 --> 17:08.348
ANYONE CLAIMING
I CUT IN?

17:08.348 --> 17:09.750
ANYONE?

17:12.593 --> 17:15.035
AND NOTE THAT THE GROUP
SUCCESSFULLY AVOIDED BEING

17:15.035 --> 17:16.316
WISHED INTO THE CORNFIELD.

17:16.316 --> 17:18.759
WHY DOES EVERYONE MAKE THAT SAME
CORNFIELD REFERENCE ABOUT ME?

17:18.759 --> 17:20.921
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET
YOU CHECKED IN, MILLY.
IT'S JUST YOU AND YOUR DAUGHTER?

17:20.921 --> 17:22.683
MY DAUGHTER'S AT
THE OTHER EVAC CENTER.

17:22.683 --> 17:25.205
‐ SERIOUSLY?
‐ TUESDAYS ARE MY NIGHT
OFF FROM THE KID.

17:25.205 --> 17:27.167
TONIGHT'S TUESDAY.
SHE'S WITH A NANNY.

17:27.167 --> 17:28.969
‐ OKAY.
‐ SHE'S GOT TOYS.

17:28.969 --> 17:32.212
EVERYBODY, MAY I HAVE
YOUR ATTENTION PLEASE?

17:32.212 --> 17:35.335
I REALLY NEED
A YOUNG BOY.

17:35.335 --> 17:38.218
OR GIRL TO VOLUNTEER
FOR SOME HEAVY LIFTING.

17:38.218 --> 17:40.621
I INCLUDE BOTH SEXES
BECAUSE IN THE PAST,

17:40.621 --> 17:42.222
MY SAYING I NEED
A YOUNG BOY

17:42.222 --> 17:43.864
LED TO A LOT OF
MISUNDERSTANDINGS.

17:43.864 --> 17:46.066
SO I'M INCLUDING
YOU LADIES AS WELL.

17:46.066 --> 17:49.309
YOU JUST NEED STRONG BACKS
AND TONED THIGHS.

17:49.309 --> 17:51.632
IF YOU FIT THE BILL,
PLEASE COME SEE ME.

17:51.632 --> 17:53.073
TO BE CLEAR,

17:53.073 --> 17:55.235
I LIKE MEN AND WOMEN
EQUALLY.

17:55.235 --> 17:57.077
BOTH SEXES WORK FOR ME.

18:00.080 --> 18:02.963
YEAH, THAT'S NOT GONNA LEAD TO
ANY MISUNDERSTANDINGS AT ALL.

18:02.963 --> 18:06.086
VOLUNTEERS. I NEED
TWO MORE VOLUNTEERS.

18:06.086 --> 18:07.487
YOU GUYS FEELINGS
STRONG TODAY?

18:07.487 --> 18:09.129
NOPE.

18:09.129 --> 18:12.252
YOU'RE DANCERS. YOU HAVE
TONED THIGHS AND NO EXCUSE.

18:12.252 --> 18:13.774
I'LL VOLUNTEER.

18:13.774 --> 18:15.495
Bash: <i>YOU'LL HAVE TO</i>
<i>WEAR THE T‐SHIRT.</i>

18:15.495 --> 18:16.617
Frankie:
<i>I'LL WEAR THE T‐SHIRT.</i>

18:16.617 --> 18:18.018
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
FIGHT ME ON THE T‐SHIRT?

18:18.018 --> 18:19.820
‐ I LIKE THE T‐SHIRT.
‐ NO ONE LIKES THE T‐SHIRT.

18:19.820 --> 18:21.101
I'LL WEAR THE T‐SHIRT.

18:21.101 --> 18:22.663
YOU CAN CHANGE BEHIND
THAT PRIVACY SCREEN.

18:47.568 --> 18:48.889
HELLO, LADIES.

18:48.889 --> 18:50.731
‐ HELLO, GIRLFRIEND.
‐ HELLO, BOYFRIEND.

18:50.731 --> 18:52.573
WHERE ARE YOU
SETTING UP?

18:52.573 --> 18:53.814
I WAS THINKING HERE.

18:53.814 --> 18:55.335
‐ IS THAT ALLOWED?
‐ NOT BY ME.

18:55.335 --> 18:56.737
WORD IS THE RULES
ARE LOOSE.

18:56.737 --> 18:57.898
COOL.

18:57.898 --> 18:59.179
HEY, GUYS.

18:59.179 --> 19:00.981
LOOKS LIKE YOU GOT A FUN
LITTLE PARTY GOING ON.

19:00.981 --> 19:02.382
WE DID,
PAST TENSE.

19:02.382 --> 19:03.584
OKAY IF I CAMP OUT HERE?

19:03.584 --> 19:05.425
KINDA GOT STUCK IN
PARENTS LAND WHERE I AM,

19:05.425 --> 19:06.827
AND THE OTHER YOUTH SECTION
IS FULL OF JOCKS

19:06.827 --> 19:07.908
