<i>♪ AIN'T GONNA QUAKE</i>
<i>I PREDICT ♪</i>

28:18.298 --> 28:21.942
<i>♪ AND SOMEBODY'S</i>
<i>GONNA DIE ♪</i>

28:21.942 --> 28:25.866
<i>♪ BUT I CAN'T</i>
<i>REVEAL WHO ♪</i>

28:25.866 --> 28:29.870
<i>♪ COLD BEER</i>
<i>WILL CURE A COLD ♪</i>

28:29.870 --> 28:31.872
<i>♪ COLD BEER AND PRETZELS ♪</i>

28:31.872 --> 28:33.874
<i>♪ TAKES CARE OF CANCER ♪</i>

28:33.874 --> 28:37.798
<i>♪ MOSCOW WILL</i>
<i>MARCH TO FRANCE ♪</i>

28:37.798 --> 28:41.882
<i>♪ THEY'LL DO</i>
<i>THE CAN‐CAN DANCE ♪</i>

28:41.882 --> 28:45.445
<i>♪ DON'T WORRY,</i>
<i>IT'LL WORK OUT ♪</i>

28:45.445 --> 28:49.610
<i>♪ MAXIM'S WILL</i>
<i>THROW THEM OUT ♪</i>

28:49.610 --> 28:53.293
<i>♪ THEY'RE GONNA STOP</i>
<i>SATURDAY NIGHT ♪</i>

28:53.293 --> 28:57.457
<i>♪ SO YOU'D BETTER HAVE</i>
<i>FUN NOW AT THE DANCE ♪</i>

28:57.457 --> 29:01.061
<i>♪ THEY'RE GONNA STOP</i>
<i>HAVING THE SUN ♪</i>

29:01.061 --> 29:03.904
<i>♪ SO YOU'D BETTER</i>
<i>GET TAN NOW ♪</i>

29:03.904 --> 29:05.385
<i>♪ AT THE DANCE ♪</i>

29:05.385 --> 29:07.508
<i>♪ AND THIS SONG</i>
<i>WILL FADE OUT ♪</i>

29:07.508 --> 29:09.469
<i>♪ YES THIS SONG</i>
<i>WILL FADE OUT ♪</i>

29:09.469 --> 29:11.431
<i>♪ THIS SONG WILL FADE OUT ♪</i>

29:13.313 --> 29:15.315
<i>♪ AND THIS SONG</i>
<i>WILL FADE OUT ♪</i>

29:15.315 --> 29:17.317
<i>♪ YES THIS SONG</i>
<i>WILL FADE OUT ♪</i>

29:17.317 --> 29:19.319
<i>♪ THIS SONG WILL FADE OUT. ♪</i>

29:19.319 --> 29:21.922
<i>( music ends )</i>

29:21.922 --> 29:23.924
<i>( cheering )</i>

29:30.130 --> 29:31.852
OH. I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU'D BE HERE.

29:31.852 --> 29:33.413
WELL, I AM.

29:33.413 --> 29:35.175
LOOK, I'M DESPERATE
TO FIND A PLACE

29:35.175 --> 29:36.777
TO GET MY MASSAGE.

29:36.777 --> 29:38.378
YOU'RE GETTING A MASSAGE
WITH ALL THAT'S GOING ON?

29:38.378 --> 29:39.860
IT'S NOT FOR PLEASURE.

29:39.860 --> 29:42.022
IT'S FOR MY PHYSICAL THERAPY
FROM MY ACCIDENT.

29:42.022 --> 29:43.664
FINE. DO IT UP HERE.

29:43.664 --> 29:45.105
COME ON IN,
FLORDELIZA.

29:48.028 --> 29:49.670
SO DO YOU WANT
FULL BODY TODAY?

29:49.670 --> 29:51.031
AROMATHERAPY,
HOT STONE,

29:51.031 --> 29:52.873
LAVENDER SCALP,
OR JUST BACK?

29:52.873 --> 29:54.875
OR SHOULDERS AND NECK?
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

29:54.875 --> 29:59.039
I WANT A MASSAGE
TO HELP HEAL MY
INJURY.

29:59.039 --> 30:00.440
SHOULDERS AND NECK.

30:00.440 --> 30:02.162
I'LL JUST BE
A SECOND.

30:05.045 --> 30:08.048
SO YOU STILL GOT
THAT HELICOPTER,
HUH?

30:08.048 --> 30:10.450
WHAT?
OH, YEAH.

30:10.450 --> 30:12.052
IT'S JUST A TIME SHARE.

30:12.052 --> 30:13.894
I BASICALLY
PAY BY THE HOUR.

30:13.894 --> 30:15.896
MUST BE EXPENSIVE.

30:15.896 --> 30:17.057
OH, PLEASE.

30:17.057 --> 30:19.059
THE FUEL SURCHARGES,

30:19.059 --> 30:22.062
THE PILOT TRAVEL TIME
CHARGES.

30:22.062 --> 30:23.704
THEY GOUGE YOU
ANY WAY THEY CAN.

30:23.704 --> 30:25.586
THANKS.

30:25.586 --> 30:26.867
FOR WHAT?

30:26.867 --> 30:28.388
YOU KNOW WHAT.

30:28.388 --> 30:31.151
WEDDINGS ARE IMPORTANT.

30:31.151 --> 30:32.513
OR SO I'VE HEARD.

30:32.513 --> 30:34.515
MOM'S REALLY ITCHING
FOR ONE OF US TO HAVE ONE.

30:34.515 --> 30:36.476
WELL, SHE SHOULD
GIVE UP ON ME.

30:36.476 --> 30:38.919
IT'S NOT IN THE CARDS.

30:38.919 --> 30:40.921
I ALWAYS THOUGHT
A HUSBAND WAS

30:40.921 --> 30:43.083
WHAT WAS MISSING
FROM MY LIFE, YOU KNOW?

30:43.083 --> 30:45.485
BUT I WASN'T
MEETING ANYBODY,

30:45.485 --> 30:47.487
AND I WANTED A BABY,

30:47.487 --> 30:49.089
SO I HAD MY
LITTLE CHING LAN

30:49.089 --> 30:50.410
SHIPPED OVER
FROM CHINA,

30:50.410 --> 30:51.972
<i>AND AFTER</i>
<i>I SIGNED FOR HER</i>

30:51.972 --> 30:54.494
AND THE NANNY TOOK
THE RIDICULOUS POINTY
HAT OFF,

30:54.494 --> 30:56.096
I JUST HELD HER.

30:56.096 --> 30:58.498
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO PUT HER DOWN.

30:58.498 --> 31:00.500
AND I REALIZED,

31:00.500 --> 31:03.103
SHE'S ALL
I'LL EVER NEED.

31:03.103 --> 31:05.105
WELL, I'M NOT GIVING UP.

31:05.105 --> 31:07.027
I'M GETTING MARRIED

31:07.027 --> 31:08.669
AND I'M KEEPING
ALL MY OPTIONS OPEN.

31:10.511 --> 31:12.633
SORRY.
LOOKING FOR MICHELLE.

31:12.633 --> 31:13.794
TOO BAD.

31:17.117 --> 31:18.999
NO.

31:20.120 --> 31:21.361
‐ HEY.
‐ YEAH?

31:21.361 --> 31:23.203
‐ CAN YOU HELP ME OUTSIDE?
‐ YEAH, SURE.

32:00.561 --> 32:02.002
IT WAS ON THE GROUND,
SO I PICKED IT UP.

32:05.005 --> 32:06.166
YOU WERE SNIFFING IT.

32:06.166 --> 32:07.568
I WAS STIFLING A YAWN.

32:07.568 --> 32:09.570
WITH HIS JACKET?
PATHETIC.

32:09.570 --> 32:11.572
‐ EXCUSE ME.
‐ NO, WAIT.

32:11.572 --> 32:14.014
LET ME TELL YOU
A STORY.

32:14.014 --> 32:18.178
LAST YEAR, MY FAMILY
WENT ON THIS PRIVATE
SAFARI.

32:18.178 --> 32:21.181
MY PARENTS, FRANKIE‐‐
IT'S SUNSET...

32:21.181 --> 32:23.023
AND WE'RE WALKING
DOWN THIS TRAIL.

32:23.023 --> 32:25.586
GOLDEN SKIES,
BEAUTIFUL VISTAS,

32:25.586 --> 32:29.429
AND WE SEE THIS
LITTLE BABY ANTELOPE
ON THE HORIZON.

32:29.429 --> 32:30.711
YEAH?

32:30.711 --> 32:33.594
WE GET CLOSER,
AND IT TURNS ITS
HEAD TO LOOK AT US.

32:33.594 --> 32:36.196
AND THE GUIDE SAYS,
"TURN AWAY.

32:36.196 --> 32:38.198
A LION'S HAD AT IT."

32:38.198 --> 32:39.600
I DON'T GET IT.

32:39.600 --> 32:41.201
IT HAD BEEN HALF
EATEN BY A LION.

32:41.201 --> 32:42.603
OH MY GOD.

32:42.603 --> 32:43.604
IT WAS HORRIBLE.

32:43.604 --> 32:45.365
EVERYBODY FROZE,
AND I THOUGHT

32:45.365 --> 32:47.207
"IT'S WRONG TO
TURN MY BACK

32:47.207 --> 32:48.609
AND LET THIS
POOR LITTLE THING

32:48.609 --> 32:50.450
JUST SIT THERE
AND BLEED OUT

32:50.450 --> 32:53.053
LIKE JUDI DENCH IN
THAT JAMES BOND MOVIE."

32:53.053 --> 32:55.415
SO I GRABBED A GUN
AND SHOT IT IN THE HEAD.

32:55.415 --> 32:58.138
YOU BLEW A BABY
ANTELOPE'S HEAD OFF?

32:58.138 --> 32:59.540
PUT IT RIGHT
OUT OF ITS MISERY.

32:59.540 --> 33:02.382
AND YOU, MY DEAR,

33:02.382 --> 33:05.025
ARE A HALF‐EATEN
BABY ANTELOPE.

33:05.025 --> 33:07.227
AND YOU'RE GONNA
SHOOT MY HEAD OFF?

33:07.227 --> 33:10.631
LOOK, IF YOU DON'T WANT
TO BE FRIENDS WITH ME,
FINE. I'M COOL.

33:10.631 --> 33:12.312
BUT I HAVE GOT
TO DO SOMETHING

33:12.312 --> 33:13.634
BECAUSE IT'S JUST
TOO SAD TO LOOK AT YOU

33:13.634 --> 33:15.235
AND I JUST CAN'T
TAKE IT ANYMORE.

33:26.246 --> 33:28.088
LET ME GUESS‐‐
YOU'RE EXCITED, NERVOUS,

33:28.088 --> 33:29.409
HAPPY AND NAUSEOUS
ALL AT ONCE?

33:29.409 --> 33:31.411
ALL FOUR EQUALLY.
SUCH A BIG DAY.

33:31.411 --> 33:32.813
OKAY, I WAS TALKING TO
THE BRIDE‐TO‐BE HERE.

33:32.813 --> 33:35.415
RIGHT. I'M SURE SHE
HAS SIMILAR FEELINGS.

33:35.415 --> 33:37.257
DID I GO TOO TRAMPY
ON THE DRESS?

33:37.257 --> 33:39.660
‐ OKAY. TURN AROUND FOR ME.
‐ I WAS SHOOTING FOR MARILYN

33:39.660 --> 33:41.341
SINGING HAPPY BIRTHDAY
TO KENNEDY,

33:41.341 --> 33:42.422
BUT WITH UNDERWEAR.

33:42.422 --> 33:44.665
‐ YOU LOOK PERFECT.
‐ THANKS.

33:44.665 --> 33:46.106
‐ <i>( phone buzzes )</i>
‐ OH NO.

33:46.106 --> 33:47.668
WHAT?

33:47.668 --> 33:49.269
‐ NO.
‐ WHAT IS IT?

33:49.269 --> 33:51.111
IT'S RICK.
HE WAS GETTING
OUT OF THE CAR

33:51.111 --> 33:52.272
AND HE TRIPPED
AND BROKE HIS ANKLE

33:52.272 --> 33:53.954
AND HE'S IN THE HOSPITAL.
IT NEVER STOPS.

33:53.954 --> 33:55.435
A BROKEN ANKLE
IS NOTHING.

33:55.435 --> 33:57.518
NO, A BROKEN ANKLE
MEANS HE'S IN A CAST
AND IN PAIN

33:57.518 --> 33:59.279
WHICH MEANS HE'S NOT
WALKING DOWN THE AISLE.

33:59.279 --> 34:02.282
‐ THIS ISN'T HAPPENING.
‐ OKAY, SO HE CAN'T WALK
DOWN THE AISLE.

34:02.282 --> 34:03.684
WE CAN WHEEL HIM
DOWN THE AISLE,

34:03.684 --> 34:05.285
OR YOU CAN GET MARRIED
AT HIS BEDSIDE.

34:05.285 --> 34:06.607
THAT'S A FUN
WEDDING STORY.

34:06.607 --> 34:08.128
I DON'T WANT TO GET
MARRIED IN A HOSPITAL.

34:08.128 --> 34:09.449
DOES THIS LOOK LIKE A DRESS
THAT YOU'D WEAR

34:09.449 --> 34:10.490
TO GET MARRIED
IN A HOSPITAL?

34:10.490 --> 34:11.532
WELL, IN A HOSPITAL
IN PARTS

34:11.532 --> 34:12.933
OF SAN FRANCISCO
PERHAPS.

34:12.933 --> 34:14.294
OR EAST VILLAGE.
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

34:14.294 --> 34:15.696
‐ CHICKIE.
‐ RICK'S BOOKIE?

34:15.696 --> 34:17.217
HIS BEST MAN.

34:17.217 --> 34:19.139
DAMN IT!
WHY ISN'T HE ANSWERING?

34:19.139 --> 34:20.300
WELL, MAYBE HE CAN'T
HEAR THE PHONE.

34:20.300 --> 34:21.782
NOT BECAUSE
HE'S OLD AND DEAF,

34:21.782 --> 34:24.064
BECAUSE THEY DON'T LET YOU
USE PHONES IN HOSPITALS.

34:24.064 --> 34:25.546
AND HE'S PROBABLY
OLD AND DEAF.

34:25.546 --> 34:26.867
OKAY, LOOK.

34:26.867 --> 34:29.149
MAYBE IN A SUPER WEIRD WAY
THIS IS A BLESSING.

34:29.149 --> 34:30.711
HOW?

34:30.711 --> 34:32.312
IT GIVES YOU
TIME TO THINK.

34:32.312 --> 34:34.394
‐ ABOUT WHAT?
‐ ABOUT THIS.

34:34.394 --> 34:35.876
‐ MARRYING RICK?
‐ YEAH.

34:35.876 --> 34:37.157
I DON'T NEED TO THINK
ABOUT MARRYING RICK.

34:37.157 --> 34:38.358
I'VE ALREADY THOUGHT
ABOUT MARRYING RICK.

34:38.358 --> 34:39.800
I KNOW YOU'RE
TIRED OF VEGAS

34:39.800 --> 34:40.881
AND THE SHOW
YOU'RE IN,

34:40.881 --> 34:42.482
AND YOUR LIFE,
AND I COMPLETELY
GET THAT.

34:42.482 --> 34:44.965
BUT MAYBE THIS ISN'T
THE ANSWER, YOU KNOW?

34:44.965 --> 34:46.406
YOU DON'T THINK I SHOULD
MARRY HIM, DO YOU?

34:46.406 --> 34:49.249
NO, I DON'T THINK
YOU SHOULD MARRY HIM.

34:49.249 --> 34:51.732
‐ WHY?
‐ HE'S...

34:51.732 --> 34:52.773
NOT CATHOLIC.

34:52.773 --> 34:54.374
JUST STOP, MICHELLE, OKAY?

34:54.374 --> 34:57.858
I MEAN, ALL THIS JUST BECAUSE
RICKY TRIPPED AND FELL?
EVERYBODY FALLS.

34:57.858 --> 34:59.820
I WATCHED YOU FALL FROM
THE TOP OF AN ESCALATOR

34:59.820 --> 35:01.622
<i>AT A MALL IN VEGAS</i>
<i>ALL THE WAY TO THE BOTTOM,</i>

35:01.622 --> 35:03.864
AND YOU BOUNCED BACK UP
AND RIGHT INTO NEIMAN'S.

35:03.864 --> 35:05.105
RICK LOVES ME.

35:05.105 --> 35:06.667
EVERYBODY LOVES YOU.

35:06.667 --> 35:08.789
YOU'RE TALIA.
YOU'RE GREAT.

35:08.789 --> 35:10.110
BUT YOU DON'T THINK
I LOVE HIM?

35:10.110 --> 35:11.592
NO.

35:11.592 --> 35:14.354
BECAUSE YOU'RE TWISTING
YOURSELF INTO A PRETZEL
FOR HIM.

35:14.354 --> 35:16.917
WITH THE CRAFTING
AND WANTING TO COOK

35:16.917 --> 35:19.439
AND WANTING A YAPPY
LITTLE PEKINGESE.
THAT'S NOT YOU.

35:19.439 --> 35:20.360
PEKINGESE AREN'T YAPPY.

35:20.360 --> 35:21.842
YEAH, THEY'RE
SUPER YAPPY.

35:21.842 --> 35:23.363
‐ THEY'RE REGAL.
‐ NO, THEY'RE NOT AT ALL REGAL.

35:23.363 --> 35:25.445
‐ BIG REGAL DOG.
‐ SMALL YAPPY SMOKE ALARMS.

35:25.445 --> 35:26.446
I DON'T WANT TO
TALK ABOUT THIS.

35:26.446 --> 35:29.369
YOU ARE TURNING DOWN
OFFERS FOR LEGIT SHOWS

35:29.369 --> 35:31.211
TO BE WITH HIM.
SHOWS THAT COULD
GO TO NEW YORK.

35:31.211 --> 35:33.373
‐ WHO DOES THAT?
‐ ME. I DO IT.

35:33.373 --> 35:35.015
I TOLD YOU,
THAT'S YOUR THING.

35:35.015 --> 35:36.296
YOU WANT TO GO BE IN
A SHOW IN NEW YORK,

35:36.296 --> 35:37.457
GO BE IN A SHOW
IN NEW YORK.

35:37.457 --> 35:38.619
I WANT TO GET MARRIED.

35:38.619 --> 35:40.861
IS THIS WHY YOU DIDN'T
WANT TO BE MY MAID OF HONOR?

35:40.861 --> 35:42.262
BECAUSE YOU THINK
THE MARRIAGE IS DOOMED?

35:42.262 --> 35:43.744
IT JUST DOESN'T
FEEL REAL TO ME.

35:43.744 --> 35:44.985
I'M PREGNANT!

35:46.386 --> 35:47.387
PRETTY REAL, HUH?

35:49.389 --> 35:51.391
OKAY.

35:51.391 --> 35:53.233
WE'LL MAKE THIS WORK.

35:53.233 --> 35:55.235
I'LL RAISE
THE BABY WITH YOU.

35:55.235 --> 35:57.037
IT'LL BE TOUGH,
BUT WE'LL MAKE IT FUN.

35:57.037 --> 35:58.879
LIKE A SITCOM.
IT'LL BE "TWO BROKE
GIRLS AND A BABY."

35:58.879 --> 36:00.040
IT'LL BE GREAT.

36:00.040 --> 36:01.562
YOU AND I AREN'T
DOING ANYTHING.

36:01.562 --> 36:02.803
I'M GETTING MARRIED.

36:02.803 --> 36:05.245
YOU DO WHATEVER.

36:05.245 --> 36:06.687
YEAH.

36:11.932 --> 36:12.933
<i>OKAY, GUYS.</i>
<i>SAY CHEESE.</i>

36:12.933 --> 36:14.214
All: CHEESE.

36:15.215 --> 36:16.617
CUTE.

36:16.617 --> 36:18.539
THAT'S GONNA LOOK GREAT
WITHOUT THE FLASH.

36:18.539 --> 36:19.700
GLAD YOU TOOK ME
UP ON THAT.

36:19.700 --> 36:20.781
( clears throat )

36:24.545 --> 36:27.387
HI, GUYS.
YOU COPING OKAY?

36:27.387 --> 36:28.949
I HAD A DOG.

36:28.949 --> 36:30.030
CALVIN.

36:30.030 --> 36:32.713
DAD NAMED HIM AFTER
SOME CARTOON GUY.

36:32.713 --> 36:34.234
"CALVIN AND HOBBES"?

36:34.234 --> 36:36.396
NO. HIS NAME
WAS JUST CALVIN.

36:36.396 --> 36:38.959
I USED TO TALK IN HIS VOICE
LIKE HE WAS THE ONE TALKING.

36:38.959 --> 36:40.561
CRACKED EVERYBODY UP.

36:40.561 --> 36:42.883
YES, YOU ARE A REGULAR
LOUIS C. K.

36:42.883 --> 36:45.966
I MISS HIM.
HE WAS A COOL DOG.

36:45.966 --> 36:47.568
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

36:47.568 --> 36:49.409
CAR HIT HIM.

36:49.409 --> 36:50.971
YEAH. YOU KNOW.

36:50.971 --> 36:53.253
WHATEVER.

36:53.253 --> 36:54.494
SO I GUESS GINNY
AND YOUR BROTHER'S

36:54.494 --> 36:55.576
NOT HAPPENING,
HUH?

36:55.576 --> 36:56.977
NOT FOR LIKE YEARS.

36:56.977 --> 36:58.418
WHAT HAPPENED?

36:58.418 --> 36:59.700
SHE'S INTO SOMEONE ELSE.

36:59.700 --> 37:01.702
WHY? CHARLIE'S COOL.

37:01.702 --> 37:02.983
IT WASN'T SO MUCH WHY,

37:02.983 --> 37:04.264
IT WAS THE WHY NOTS.

37:04.264 --> 37:05.746
AND SHE LIKES
THIS OTHER GUY.

37:05.746 --> 37:07.548
HUH.

37:07.548 --> 37:10.070
KINDA THOUGHT FOR A WHILE
THERE'D BE A DOUBLE‐DATE
THING OR SOMETHING.

37:10.070 --> 37:11.552
YOU MEAN YOU AND ME?

37:11.552 --> 37:12.753
YEAH.

37:12.753 --> 37:13.914
NO.

37:13.914 --> 37:16.557
‐ WHY NOT?
‐ BECAUSE.

37:16.557 --> 37:18.999
MY MOM SAYS
BECAUSE IS A WORD,

37:18.999 --> 37:20.120
NOT A REASON.

37:20.120 --> 37:22.683
WELL, THAT'S THE REASON.

37:22.683 --> 37:24.004
BECAUSE, OKAY?

37:24.004 --> 37:25.165
BECAUSE.

37:25.165 --> 37:27.768
SO YOU CAN'T THINK
OF A REASON WHY?

37:27.768 --> 37:29.890
I DON'T KNOW.

37:29.890 --> 37:32.012
IF YOU CAN'T THINK
OF A REASON WHY,

37:32.012 --> 37:35.375
CAN YOU THINK OF
A REASON WHY NOT?

37:38.619 --> 37:39.980
NOT OFFHAND.

37:39.980 --> 37:44.545
THEN WHY NOT?

37:54.034 --> 37:55.636
HEY, BRIDE.

37:55.636 --> 37:57.638
LOOK.
IT'S A PEKINGESE.

37:57.638 --> 37:59.800
RICK BROUGHT HIM.
ONE OF MY WEDDING GIFTS.

37:59.800 --> 38:01.642
‐ OH.
‐ YOU WERE RIGHT.

38:01.642 --> 38:03.403
I WAS THINKING
OF ANOTHER DOG.

38:03.403 --> 38:04.725
YEAH, BUT THIS
ONE'S GOOD TOO.

38:04.725 --> 38:06.326
AND IN A PINCH
YOU CAN DUST WITH IT.

38:06.326 --> 38:07.728
I GUESS.

38:07.728 --> 38:08.809
HEY, HE'S ADORABLE.

38:08.809 --> 38:11.011
YEAH.
HE KIND OF IS.

38:12.653 --> 38:13.854
YOU STILL WANT ME
IN YOUR WEDDING?

38:13.854 --> 38:16.657
YOU'RE TECHNICALLY
NOT IN THE WEDDING.

38:16.657 --> 38:18.498
WOULD YOU TAKE HIM
A SECOND?

38:18.498 --> 38:19.860
OH.

38:21.662 --> 38:22.983
YES, YOU'RE IN
THE WEDDING.

38:22.983 --> 38:24.144
AFTER ALL THAT
STUFF I SAID?

38:24.144 --> 38:25.666
YOU SAID IT BECAUSE
YOU WORRY ABOUT ME.

38:25.666 --> 38:27.067
AND THERE'S
EVERY REASON TO.

38:27.067 --> 38:29.670
LOOK AT HIM.
HE IS OLD.

38:29.670 --> 38:31.071
OLDER.
NOT OLD.

38:31.071 --> 38:32.352
HE'S IN A WHEELCHAIR.

38:32.352 --> 38:34.675
TEMPORARILY.
THE ANKLE WILL HEAL.

38:34.675 --> 38:36.517
I DON'T WANT TO
BE A YOUNG WIDOW.

38:36.517 --> 38:37.678
LIKE ME?

38:37.678 --> 38:39.520
NO.

38:39.520 --> 38:41.361
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

38:41.361 --> 38:43.083
I HAD NO TIME
WITH HUBBELL.

38:43.083 --> 38:45.686
24 HOURS.

38:45.686 --> 38:47.848
BUT IT WAS A PRETTY
GREAT 24 HOURS.

38:47.848 --> 38:48.969
YEAH.

38:48.969 --> 38:51.171
YOU'LL HAVE TIME.

38:51.171 --> 38:52.693
DO I LOOK OKAY?

38:52.693 --> 38:54.174
DO YOU LOOK OKAY?

38:54.174 --> 38:55.536
‐ YOU MAY KILL HIM
WITH THAT LOOK.
‐ MICHELLE.

38:55.536 --> 38:56.697
I MEAN IT.
CROSS YOUR EYES

38:56.697 --> 38:58.018
